<DOC><DOCNO> AP880810-0084 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-10-88 0859EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p PM-NewContract     08-10 0113</FIRST><SECOND>PM-New Contract,0117</SECOND><HEAD>Transit Pact OK'd in New Orleans; Strike During Convention Averted</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The city's bus and streetcar drivers haveapproved a new contract, averting a strike before next week'sRepublican National Convention.   The Amalgamated Transit Union said drivers approved thethree-year contract Tuesday. Vote totals were not released.   The union represents more than 600 of the 700 bus and streetcardrivers.   Negotiators for the union and the Regional Transit Authorityreached a tentative agreement Sunday night, hours before a strikedeadline of 12:01 a.m. Monday.   Top pay for drivers is now $10.10 an hour. Under the newcontract, that will rise in steps to $10.50 by 1991.</TEXT></DOC>